    {"course_id": 3, "title": "Fuel & Lubrication Safety", "content": "## Fuel & Lubrication Safety\n\n### Fuel Safety\n**NEVER:**\n- Smoke near fuel\n- Overfill tank (allow expansion space)\n- Spill fuel (clean immediately)\n- Store fuel in inappropriate containers\n\n**DO:**\n- Turn off engine when refueling\n- Use correct fuel grade\n- Check for leaks regularly\n\n### Lubrication\nLubricate regularly:\n- Chain (every 500 km)\n- Cables (throttle, clutch, brake)\n- Pivot points\n\nProper lubrication reduces wear, improves performance, and extends component life.", "order": 19},
